Title: World in Union
Comment:
Imagine this: It’s 1995 — just a year after apartheid ended. The country is still uncertain, divided, holding its breath for what this new South Africa might become. Then, through rugby — a sport that once symbolized separation — something extraordinary happens.

When Nelson Mandela steps onto the field in a Springbok jersey and Francois Pienaar lifts the World Cup trophy, the entire nation erupts. People of all races cheer, cry, and hug strangers. For a moment, every barrier falls away.

It’s not just a victory — it’s healing, hope, and pride.
For the first time, South Africans feel it deep within — one team, one country, one heartbeat.
